Join a thriving startup and TechStars graduate. DigitalOcean is simplifying the complexities of cloud hosting. We are focused on building the next cloud that will revolutionize the hosting industry. We are a small team but growing at a very rapid pace with over 90,000 virtual servers launched and 4,500+ customers.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
We currently manage over 1,000 servers in our New York and Amsterdam datacenter locations, store over a petabyte of data on our network growing at 1.5 terabytes a day, and deliver gigabits of active network throughput to the public internet.</p>
<p>
We are searching for an experienced systems engineer who&#39;s looking to take on a new challenge. You&#39;ll be responsible for growing the company&#39;s open source infrastructure and motivating the engineers who currently provide 24/7 service.</p>
<p>
We have a tight knit team that loves to have fun, food and drinks. We work hard when we need to and we enjoy the slow periods. Our office is located in the middle of SoHo so there&#39;s plenty to do after work.</p>
<p>
The new year has plenty of challenges in store and we&#39;re looking for the right leader to complement a fast and growing team. In the new year we are building cutting edge technology to deliver a whole new set of services.</p>
<p>
<strong>What you need to know:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience in large datacenter environments (250+ nodes)</li>
<li>
Experience with high traffic redundant BGP networks (1+ Gbps)</li>
<li>
Virtualization (Xen/KVM)</li>
<li>
Storage (ZFS, iSCSI, Gluster)</li>
<li>
Configuration Management (Puppet/Chef)</li>
<li>
Managing teams and culture building (5+ people)</li>
<li>
Agile development</li>
<li>
Automation (deployment, production &amp; scripting)</li>
</ul>
